-- Mexico Stocks: Cemex, Penoles, Grupo Mexico Were Active
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-03-20T21:51:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/mexico-stocks-cemex-penoles-grupo-mexico-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index fell 0.5 percent to 38,055.27.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)  , the largest cement maker in the
Americas, rose 3.9 percent to 9.93 pesos. Cemex advanced as data
showed housing starts in the U.S., the company’s biggest foreign
market, hovered near a three-year high in February and building
permits rose, adding to signs that the industry is stabilizing.  Mexican mining companies fell in line with metal prices on
signs of slower growth in  China .  Grupo Mexico SAB (GMEXICOB)  , the country’s largest
mining company, declined 1.3 percent to 40.55 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES*)  (PE&OLES* MM), the nation’s biggest
silver producer, fell 0.8 percent to 599.42 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
